  <prompt>
    Close out the `sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2` project. This is the final task — no new functional work; project hygiene + retrospective + r3 scope recommendation.

    Seven wrap-up actions (per task-create SKILL.md Step 3.7):

    1. **Final quality gates**: invoke `/code-review` on all project code (Phase 1-5 production fixes); invoke `/adr-check` on all project code; fix any critical issues surfaced (HIGH findings only — MED/LOW deferred to r3).

    2. **Repo hygiene**: invoke `/repo-cleanup projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2` (cleans `notes/debug/`, `notes/spikes/`, `notes/drafts/`; archives `notes/handoffs/`; validates structure compliance).

    3. **README.md update**: status → "Complete"; last-updated → today; phase → "Complete"; progress → 100%; completed-date → today; check all graduation criteria boxes; add changelog entry.

    4. **plan.md update**: status → "Complete"; all milestone statuses → ✅ done.

    5. **Lessons-learned**: create `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/notes/lessons-learned.md` with r2 calibration data (what went well; what was harder than expected; sibling coordination outcomes; recommendations for any future closure project).

    6. **Exit-ledger**: create `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/ledgers/exit-ledger.md` with cumulative r2 state — all 20 entries' final disposition; cluster-wise summary; r3 recommendation per D-06 (whether r3 is warranted, scope sketch if so).

    7. **Final verification**: confirm all task files marked completed in TASK-INDEX.md; confirm no critical code-review issues outstanding; confirm `/repo-cleanup` completed without blocking findings.

    Hard dependency: tasks 083 (PR merged to master) + 084 (doc-drift audit PASS) MUST be complete before this task runs.

    NO production code changes in this task. NO test changes. Hygiene + retrospective only.
  </prompt>

  <role>AI agent closing out the r2 project with final quality gates, repo-cleanup, README/plan updates, lessons-learned, exit-ledger, and final verification.</role>

