  <context>
    <background>
      The r2 wrap-up follows the pattern established by r1 task 090 (closed 2026-05-31): final quality gates + repo-cleanup + README/plan updates + lessons-learned + exit-ledger + final verification.

      Key r2-specific contributions to capture in the lessons-learned:
      - Inversion of NFR-01 worked cleanly (r1 was test-only; r2 was production-side; the inversion did NOT cause confusion because design.md §D-01 was explicit)
      - Cluster exception (D-02) closed 4 ledger entries via 1 fix — confirms r1's cluster-classification pattern scales
      - Phase 4 5-track parallel dispatch (per D-04 pilot-grade) — measure whether the parallel-track model worked or whether sequential tracks would have been simpler
      - Anti-drift effectiveness finding (FR-09 / NFR-07) — was the empirical evidence high or low compliance? What does that tell us about D-05's design choice?
      - TestClock PoC outcome — did it work cleanly in `Services/Workspace/*`? Is r3 generalization warranted?
      - Mutation testing pilot outcome — what's the mutation score for `Services/Ai/Safety/*`? Is r3 expansion to Capabilities + Chat warranted?
      - PCF/Code Pages audit outcome — is the BFF rot pattern present on the client side? r3 scope recommendation.
      - Coverlet baseline — useful for r3 threshold gate calibration

      The exit-ledger is the cumulative r2 close artifact — referenced for years by future projects. Quality matters. Use r1's exit-ledger as the structural template.

      r3 recommendation per D-06: NOT pre-committed; the recommendation derives from r2 audit findings. If pilots scored well, r3 may not be needed. If pilots surfaced significant issues, r3 scope is well-motivated. Owner decides.
    </background>
