  <steps>
    <step order="1">**Final quality gates**: Invoke `/code-review` skill against all Phase 1-3 production-fix PRs (or against the cumulative project diff). Invoke `/adr-check` skill against all `src/` changes from r2. Capture skill outputs. Fix any HIGH severity findings; document MED/LOW findings in lessons-learned as r3 carry-forward.</step>
    <step order="2">**Repo hygiene**: Invoke `/repo-cleanup projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2` skill per its SKILL.md. Capture output. Remove ephemeral files (`notes/debug/`, `notes/spikes/`, `notes/drafts/`); archive `notes/handoffs/` to date-stamped subdirectory.</step>
    <step order="3">**README.md update**: Edit `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/README.md`:
      - Status header: "🟢 Active" or current → "✅ Complete"
      - Last-updated: today's date
      - Phase: "Complete"
      - Progress: 100%
      - Completed-date: today
      - Check all 12-14 graduation criteria boxes (cross-reference spec.md §Success Criteria)
      - Add changelog entry: "2026-08-XX (date): project closed; 20 ledger entries closed; Phase 4 5-track deliverables published; final triple-run PASS; PR merged"
    </step>
    <step order="4">**plan.md update**: Edit `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/plan.md`:
      - Status: → "Complete"
      - All milestone statuses (Phase 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5): → ✅ done
    </step>
    <step order="5">**Lessons-learned**: Write `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/notes/lessons-learned.md` with these sections:
      (a) **Header**: project name, closure date, person-hours actual vs estimate, wall-clock actual vs estimate (2026-06-01 → 2026-08-31)
      (b) **What went well**: NFR-01 inversion worked cleanly; cluster exception (D-02) successful; parallel Phase 4 5-track dispatch outcome; ledger lifecycle held up under r2 use
      (c) **What was harder than expected**: any Phase 1-3 production fix that took longer than estimated; sibling-coordination friction if any; Phase 4 track that surprised
      (d) **Sibling-coordination outcomes**: per FR-06 — Action Engine / Insights / Communications outreach outcomes; any commitments persisting post-r2
      (e) **Anti-drift effectiveness reflection**: per FR-09 / NFR-07 — empirical compliance rate; what it says about D-05 design choice
      (f) **Phase 4 pilot reflections**: per-track outcome (audit findings, mutation score, TestClock PoC success/issues, Coverlet baseline, anti-drift report findings)
      (g) **r3 recommendation rationale**: per D-06 — based on r2 findings, is r3 warranted? scope sketch if yes; defer-or-skip rationale if no
      (h) **Carry-forward items**: anything r2 intentionally didn't do (per D-04); MED/LOW code-review findings; P2/P3 doc-drift items
    </step>
    <step order="6">**Exit-ledger**: Write `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/ledgers/exit-ledger.md` (NEW file) with these sections:
      (a) **Project overview**: dates, scope, predecessor link, total tasks executed
      (b) **20 entries' final disposition table**: per RB-T044-* and RB-T028-*, final status (`repaired` / `transferred-to-sibling` / `archived-as-dead-target`), resolution mode, ledger entry cross-reference to r1's real-bug-ledger.md
      (c) **Cluster-wise summary**: HIGH (5 entries; resolution by cluster); MED (7 entries); LOW (8 entries)
      (d) **Coverlet baseline % per project**: copied from `baseline/coverlet-baseline-2026-08-XX.md` (task 043 output)
      (e) **Phase 4 deliverable cross-references**: audit, mutation, TestClock, anti-drift links + brief outcome statements
      (f) **Final triple-run summary**: cross-reference to `baseline/final-triple-run-2026-08-XX.md` (task 082 output)
      (g) **r3 scope recommendation**: per D-06 — derivative of r2 audit findings; explicit recommendation (commission r3 / defer r3 / skip r3); rationale
    </step>
    <step order="7">**Final verification**:
      - Read `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md` — confirm all task rows show ✅ (or appropriate completion marker)
      - Verify no critical (HIGH severity) code-review issues outstanding from Step 1
      - Verify `/repo-cleanup` Step 2 output had no blocking findings
      - Update `current-task.md`: phase → "✅ Complete — project closed YYYY-MM-DD"; last-updated → today; current-task → "none — project closed"; next-action → "none — see `notes/lessons-learned.md` for r3 recommendation"
      - Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: task 090 row → ✅; "Project COMPLETE" header line appended
    </step>
    <step order="8">Verify `git status` shows only files in `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/` modified (README, plan, current-task, TASK-INDEX, lessons-learned, exit-ledger; possibly other cleanup-artifact files from `/repo-cleanup`). NO unintended `src/`, `.claude/`, `.github/` modifications.</step>
    <step order="9">Step 9.5 — Run `code-review` + `adr-check` on the cumulative project diff (FULL rigor for wrap-up). Verify no HIGH findings remain. Document any deferred MED/LOW in lessons-learned § (h) Carry-forward.</step>
    <step order="10">Final commit: "chore(close): sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2 project — 20 ledger entries closed, Phase 4 pilots published, lessons-learned + exit-ledger". Push to remote per `push-to-github` skill. Note: master already has the cumulative project commit from task 083; this is a small wrap-up follow-up commit.</step>
  </steps>

